item.title: The Essential Role of Buyer Agents in Today's Real Estate Market
item.description: In the ever-evolving world of real estate, recent changes in buyer agent compensation have shifted the landscape. Instead of a predetermined fee, compensation is now negotiated during the offer process following a recent NAR settlement. However, this adjustment doesn't eradicate buyer agent compensation; it simply modifies the procedure. For buyers, this alteration underscores the importance of loyalty.
